Consider the following class definition.

```java
public class Counter {
    private int count;

    public Counter(int count) {
        count = count;
    }

    public int getCount() { return count; }
}
```

What is printed by the following client code?

```java
Counter c = new Counter(10);
System.out.println(c.getCount());
```

What is the output of the following code?

```java
public class Temperature {
    private double degrees;

    public Temperature() {
        degrees = 98.6;
    }

    public Temperature(double d) {
        degrees = d;
    }

    public double getDegrees() { return degrees; }
}

Temperature t1 = new Temperature();
Temperature t2 = new Temperature(100.0);
System.out.println(t1.getDegrees() + " " + t2.getDegrees());
```

A programmer intends `Rectangle(int l, int w)` to be a constructor, but the class behaves unexpectedly. Which of the following best explains the problem?

```java
public class Rectangle {
    private int length;
    private int width;

    public void Rectangle(int l, int w) {
        length = l;
        width = w;
    }

    public int area() { return length * width; }
}

Rectangle r = new Rectangle(5, 3);
```

Determine the values of `x` and `y` after the following code executes.

```java
public class Point {
    private int x;
    private int y;

    public Point(int x, int y) {
        this.x = x + 1;
        this.y = y * 2;
    }

    public int getX() { return x; }
    public int getY() { return y; }
}

Point p = new Point(3, 4);
int x = p.getX();
int y = p.getY();
```

What is the output of the following code?

```java
public class Ticket {
    private String event;
    private int price;

    public Ticket(String e) {
        event = e;
        price = 50;
    }

    public Ticket(String e, int p) {
        event = e;
        price = p;
    }

    public String getInfo() {
        return event + ": $" + price;
    }
}

Ticket t1 = new Ticket("Concert");
Ticket t2 = new Ticket("Game", 75);
System.out.println(t1.getInfo());
System.out.println(t2.getInfo());
```

What is the output of the following code?

```java
public class Jar {
    private int cookies;

    public Jar() {
        cookies = 0;
    }

    public Jar(int n) {
        cookies = n;
    }

    public void add(int n) { cookies += n; }
    public int getCookies() { return cookies; }
}

Jar j1 = new Jar(5);
Jar j2 = new Jar();
j1.add(3);
j2.add(j1.getCookies());
System.out.println(j1.getCookies() + " " + j2.getCookies());
```

Consider the following class definition.

```java
public class Lamp
{
    private String color;
    private boolean on;

    public Lamp(String c)
    {
        color = c;
        on = false;
    }

    public Lamp(String c, boolean state)
    {
        color = c;
        on = state;
    }

    public String status()
    {
        return color + ": " + on;
    }
}
```

Determine the output of the following code.

```java
Lamp x = new Lamp("green", false);
Lamp y = new Lamp("yellow");
System.out.println(x.status());
System.out.println(y.status());
```

Consider the following class definition.

```java
public class Rectangle
{
